article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. -- — Quimari Peterson scored 22 points as East Tennessee State beat Queens 82-67 on Sunday night. Peterson added five rebounds for the Buccaneers (4-2). Karon Boyd scored 20 points and added eight rebounds. Davion Bradford shot 4 of 5 from the field and 6 for 8 from the line to finish with 14 points, while adding nine rebounds. Leo Colimerio led the way for the Royals (3-4) with 20 points. Chris Ashby added 15 points for Queens. Asjon Anderson also had nine points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
